{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"viperous-united-whooper","description":"## What\nAdd four Claude Code skills as worked examples of agentic development workflows with rebar, under\n`examples/claude-skills/`: `rebar-brainstorm`, `rebar-debug`, `rebar-implement`, `rebar-janitor`\n(each a `SKILL.md` plus supporting reference files), and a `README.md` explaining the examples.\n\n## Why\nShow contributors one concrete way agents can plan, implement, debug, and maintain code using rebar\nas the system of record. Illustrative only — rebar does not depend on these skills.\n\n## Scope\n- Docs/examples only, under `examples/claude-skills/`; no changes to `src/` or runtime behavior.\n- Content is self-contained: no absolute paths, home dirs, personal identifiers, hosts, or secrets.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `examples/claude-skills/` contains rebar-brainstorm, rebar-debug, rebar-implement, and\n      rebar-janitor skill directories plus a `README.md`.\n- [ ] No personal / user / host / secret / absolute-path leakage in committed content.\n- [ ] `rebar-implement`'s review-and-land steps defer to project docs (rebar/Gerrit as the default).\n- [ ] Change lands on `main` via Gerrit with `LLM-Review +1` and `Verified +1`.","id":"e229-6fae-bd13-47bd","parent_id":"","priority":3,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Add example Claude Code skills under examples/claude-skills/"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783712431682647001,"uuid":"be5551fd-3520-4399-a029-13f1560f085b"}